-- Bear Stearns to buy Ford finance arm in India: report
-- 
-- Wed Aug 15, 2007 5:30am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/15/us-fordfinancial-bearstearns-acquisition-idUSBOM4720620070815

 

 MUMBAI  (Reuters) - Bear, Stearns & Co. Inc. BSC.N plans to enter India by acquiring the financial arm of U.S.-based automaker Ford Motor Co. ( F.N ), the Economic Times newspaper said in an unsourced story on Wednesday. 

 Bear Stearns will buy the financial arm, Ford Automotive Finance Co., for 900 million rupees ($22.09 million), the newspaper said. It plans to invest 1 billion rupees ($24.54 million) to comply with the Indian regulations and start a full-fledged financial services company, the report said. On Tuesday, Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc. LEH.N agreed to buy the institutional equities business of Indian brokerage Brics Securities for an undisclosed sum. India has about 1,050 registered foreign institutional investors and data from the market regulator Securities & Exchange Board of India showed, with 32 asset management firms managing over 4 trillion rupees ($99 billion) worth of assets. The list of foreign institutional investors operating in India include Citigroup ( C.N ), UBS ( UBSN.VX ), Morgan Stanley ( MS.N ) and Goldman Sachs ( GS.N ). ($1=40.75 Indian rupees)